What will I be responsible for in this job? (brief summary of the role)

The Business Intelligence Analyst is a balanced technical and business role. Individuals within the Business Intelligence Analyst role will be responsible for the identification of business intelligence, reporting, and data analysis needs as well as the design and implementation of technical solutions. They will work closely with clients and IT teams to turn data into critical information, knowledge and insight that can be used to make informed business decisions. It is essential that this individual build an understanding of the business at a level of detail that enables them to identify and address critical issues. They provide data that is accurate, congruent and reliable, and ensure the information is easily available to users for direct consumption. The Business Intelligence Analyst will educate and train clients to use the data as an analytical tool, displaying the information in new forms for the purpose of analysis and data exploration.

The Business Intelligence Analyst will work with clients to determine business requirements, priorities, define Key Performance Indicators (KPI), develop Business Intelligence and Data Analytics strategy and governance. This includes working with business and development teams to design, and document dashboards, alerts, and reports. This individual is accountable for providing leadership and independent initiatives in facilitating information gathering, structured documentation and presentation of findings to all levels of management.

The Business Intelligence Analyst will understand how data is turned into information and knowledge and how that knowledge supports and enables positive business change. They must have an in-depth understanding of the business environment and an interest in going beyond the obvious, delving into the source, the definition, philosophy, and foundational roots of a data element in order to create information. They must work well within a team environment and must also work on their own initiative.

What are the requirements?
Years of experience: 2 years of relevant experience
Education: Bachelors degree relevant to this role
Physical requirements: General Office

What critical skills are needed for you to consider someone for this position?

Demonstrated understanding and ability with statistics
Proficient with SQL, able to efficiently write queries to retrieve data
Proficient with SQL Server Integration Services
Experience with a scripting language like Python
Experience with Spotfire
Mastery with Microsoft Excel
Proficient with a Statistical Language (R, SAS, SPSS)
Accountable for information gathering, structured documentation, and presentation of findings to all levels of management;
Excellent, communication and interpersonal skills are essential;
Excellent presentation and reporting skills are essential;

What other skills/experience would be helpful to have?

Critical, analytic and strategic thinking: Identifies issues, trends and provides practical recommendations through comprehensive analysis and application of technical and business skills
Innovative: Contributes, promotes, and adopts new ideas and approaches;
Teamwork & Collaboration: Able and willing to work in a cross-functional team environment.
Work well with others who may not be proficient with statistics and supporting technologies;
Planning and Organization: Displays initiative. Demonstrates the ability to prioritize tasks. Has the ability to multitask. Well organized plans in advance;
Goal Orientation: Persistence, drive, and energy directed to the achievement of well-defined goals;

How much should I expect to travel?

Travel is expected to be minimal but during the initial deployment phase, it could be 25% - 50% of the time.

Following the implementation phase of the program, it is expected that travel will be less than 25% of the time.

Employees in roles that require travel will need to be able to qualify for a company credit card or be able to use their own personal credit card for travel expenses and submit for reimbursement.

Collaborate with clients to determine business requirements, priorities, define key performance indicators (KPI), and develop Business Intelligence and Data Analytics strategy;
Working with the program team on the design of dashboards, alerts, and reports;
Conduct analyses of functional business processes and functional business requirements and participate in the development of business cases in the support of process changes and/or Business Intelligence and Data Analytics projects;
Work with current and prospective clients and building long lasting relationships with them;
Support the transformation program staff by responding to service requests from clients;
