ARCH US MI Services, Inc., is seeking a Manager, Business Intelligence in Greensboro, NC.



Job Duties:                              



Develop strong relationships with business community, information technology organization and vendors, utilizing deep understanding of current business processes, industry best practices, and technical knowledge of data warehousing.
Define and maintain technical architecture for data warehouse and business intelligence infrastructure by:
Using various skills, methodologies, tools and technologies such as: Microsoft SQL Server, data profiling, data mapping, data modeling the Enterprise Data Warehouse, from source systems.
BI solutions using ETL and reporting/visualization tools. 
Agile or iterative SDLC methodologies with focus on short release cycles, BI tools such as Cognos, Power BI, Tableau, SSRS, SAS Visual Analytics, Microstrategy;
Data technologies such as My SQL, MongoDB, Cassandra, Kudu.
Identify and make recommendations for mid- and long-term improvements to enhance stability, efficiency, and consistency of technical infrastructure.
Work with Digital Product Manager and other parties to agree on and establish priorities.
Prepare and maintain project and resource schedules within the agile framework/Jira.
Utilize sophisticated knowledge of data warehouse and software engineering principles, monitor progress of technical projects, confer with project engineers and review reports to ensure that development is progressing according to schedule, cost estimates and guidelines.
Participate actively in resolution of critical software related issues.
Collaborate with business community and IT colleagues to define an enterprise data model and business intelligence architecture supporting multiple subject areas.
Motivate, grow and lead team that provides daily production support, maintenance, and minor enhancements.
Ensure end-to-end resolution of problems.




Qualifications:              Master’s degree (or foreign equivalent) in Computer Science, Computer Information Systems or related field of study plus 3 years of experience as Software Engineer, Data Warehouse Architect or related position.



Must have 3 years of experience with:

Data Modeling;
Design and development of Enterprise Data Warehouse with flexible, scalable and high performance data architectures;
Data profiling and data mapping from source systems to Enterprise Data Warehouse;
Designing BI solutions using Enterprise Data Warehouse and Cognos;
Designing and developing ETL solutions using SSIS or other similar ETL tools;
Microsoft SQL Server;
Agile or iterative SDLC methodologies with focus on short release cycles;
Must have 3 years of combined experience with at least 2 of the following BI tools: Cognos, PowerBI, Tableau, SAS Visual Analytics, Microstrategy;

Must have 3 years of combined experience with at least 2 of the following data technologies: DB2, Oracle, MongoDB, MySQL;
